# 13. 「誰の味方なの？」

Honami: (I haven't seen Saki around in a while.)
Honami: (I wonder if something happened. Could she have had a relapse?)
Honami: Oh... Ichika...
Ichika: What's up, Honami? What are you doing in front of my classroom?
Honami: I, um...wanted to ask you about Saki. I noticed she's been absent lately. Did she have to go back to the hospital?
Ichika: No, she just has a persistent cold. I went to her house to see her yesterday. Her fever's finally gone down.
Honami: Oh, really? I'm glad it's nothing serious.
Ichika: I saw Tsukasa, too, for the first time in ages.
Ichika: He put on his own one-man musical to cheer Saki up and make her feel better.
Honami: Hehe... He never changes.
Honami: Ah!
Ichika: For a moment, you talked to me normally again. That was nice.
Honami: .....
Ichika: Honami, listen...
Ichika: Shiho joined our band. She explained about why she'd been acting so cold and distant.
Honami: Oh, really...
Ichika: Are you sure you wouldn't like to join us too? That you don't want to hang out with us again?
Honami: .....
Ichika: Sorry. I'm one to talk...
Ichika: I wasn't there for you when you were going through a rough time, so I can't expect you to want to be friends with me now.
Honami: Don't say that!
Honami: You've done nothing wrong, Ichika.
Ex-Classmate A: Honami, mind if I rant a bit? This other girl from my club was sooo mean to me. Listen...
Honami: So that's what happened. Are you okay? Try to calm down.
Ex-Classmate B: And like, how could she say that to my face? What did I do to deserve that?
Honami: Oh, I see... That's kind of sad to hear...
Ex-Classmate C: Honami, you got a moment? I need to talk to you.
Honami: Yes, sure. What do you want to talk about?
Ex-Classmate C: I heard you were talking crap about me after class yesterday.
Honami: What? I'd never...
Honami: Two girls from my school club were kicking up a fuss over what I said to them. You agreed with them, no?
Ex-Classmate C: Whose side are you on?
Honami: I... I wasn't taking sides...
Ex-Classmate C: I heard that you always tell people what they want to hear. Some people-pleaser you are.
Honami: That's not what I was...
Honami: It's just that... It's hard to not have anyone to talk to when you're hurt. I thought it would help them...
Ex-Classmate C: A friend to everybody is a friend to nobody.
Ex-Classmate C: You thought you could make everybody like you by nodding and smiling at anything they say, huh?
Honami: No, it wasn't like that...
Ichika: Honami...
Honami: Oh, Ichika...
Ichika: Are you sure you're all right?
Ichika: If you don't want to talk now, that's fine, but know that you can always count on me. That's what friends are for.
Honami: Thank you, Ichika...
Ex-Classmate B: I saw Honami chatting to some friend in the hallway. I swear she was complaining we're bullying her here.
Ex-Classmate C: Pfft! I gave her a piece of my mind for being such a bootlicker and now she's acting all hurt.
Ex-Classmate C: She just wants to play the victim. That friend of hers is just the same, taking her side without even bothering to find out what happened.
Ex-Classmate A: I see Honami talking to that girl all the time. Her name's Hoshino.
Honami: !!
Ichika: Hey, Honami! Want to walk home together? There's a new bakery we could stop by on the way.
Honami: I'm sorry, Ichika...
Honami: Please don't talk to me at school anymore.
Ichika: What? Why don't you want to talk to me?
Honami: I already made up with my classmates, so you don't have to worry about me. Okay?
Ichika: Honami, I don't get it... Wait!
Ichika: I knew it. I shouldn't have just left you like that.
Honami: You offered to help, and that counts. Thank you.
Honami: But... I'm scared, you know?
Honami: I don't want my classmates to whisper things behind my back, or laugh at me, or ignore me.
Honami: It felt so awful, and I don't want to go through that ever again!
Ichika: .....
Honami: I don't want them to call me a bootlicker, or a people-pleaser who's friends with everybody, and friends with nobody.
Honami: So... I decided to prove my loyalty to them by not having friends outside our class.
Ichika: You can't be serious!
Ichika: What they said to you was just nasty! You're kind to everyone and there's nothing wrong with that. I know you, Honami, they don't!
Honami: I'm sorry, Ichika...
Honami's Classmate A: Honami! The school store was almost sold out of buns, so I bought all they had left for us all to share!
Honami's Classmate B: These custard buns are all the rage! Huh? Honami, are you coming?
Honami: Sorry, I've got to go.
Ichika: Wait!
Honami: I...don't even know what friendship is anymore.
